docs.lead_paragraph: CHICAGO, Aug. 19.--The WatkinsBamberger baby controversy reached a settlement late today that promised to be final, when the mothers of the boys born June 30 in the Englewood Hospital amicably exchanged babies, shook hands and promised each other they would bicker no more. Health Commissioner Kegel officiated as master of ceremonies.

headline.main: Chicago Baby Mix-Up Settled by Exchange; Bambergers Live Up Child on Experts' Ruling

docs.abstract: Baby mix-up settled when they exchange babies with Bambergers according to experts' ruling
